  "pipeType": "open",
  "notes": "Best-effort starting point for a Margaret James style bamboo treble pipe in C, modeled here as a straight three-hole open pipe/tabor-pipe family instrument rather than a recorder. Assumptions: cylindrical to very slightly tapered bamboo bore, integral blowing end, total sounding length about 330 mm, fundamental all-closed note C5 at A440 and 20 C, second-register octave overblow available through the new open-pipe model. Hole layout is intentionally conservative and should be treated as a prototyping baseline rather than a finished historical copy. If you want, the next pass should tune the three hole diameters and z positions against a target diatonic scale and then shape the outside diameters to match a specific Margaret James specimen more closely."
